<Note rev:revStatus="R">
<Para>
<?FTID-rev start?>The enroute climb weight penalties are based on single engine  <?FTID-rev end?><?FTID-rev start?> operating speeds that approximate maximum lift-to-drag ratio  <?FTID-rev end?><?FTID-rev start?> speed. To account for the difference in level-off altitude when  <?FTID-rev end?><?FTID-rev start?> operating at other speeds, multiply the enroute climb weight  <?FTID-rev end?><?FTID-rev start?> penalty listed above by the appropriate factor
listed on page  <?FTID-rev end?><?FTID-rev start?> 3.00-01-00.2 in the ENROUTE DIVERSION SPEED EFFECTS  <?FTID-rev end?><?FTID-rev start?> paragraph.  <?FTID-rev end?></Para>
</Note>
